{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fa816734-be4f-4a54-9bf2-99ab1402640a","content":"Since you already have the dump file, you need a **dump analysis** tool rather than a collection tool. Here's how to analyze it:\n\n### Using `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show last exception details |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `setthread <id>` then `clrstack` | Inspect other threads |\n\n### Using LLDB (Linux)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-sos\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\n\n### Quick triage flow\n1. Run `pe` to check for an unhandled exception\n2. Run `clrthreads` to find faulting thread\n3. Run `clrstack` on that thread for the stack trace\n\nWould you like help running any of these commands on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"39dda71d-e1c6-43ea-b039-bb5ba874053a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should NOT invoke that skill.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their crash dump.","outputTokens":398,"requestId":"9813:1521D2:D7AB75:FC304E:69F40800"},"id":"e6fe76b0-18f8-4a35-b7e7-f90ebd12057f","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:55:22.823Z","parentId":"9846fa9a-4ec8-4b24-9480-21ecb69fac3f"}
